[QC suspect] UPDATED 2020-08-31: The vendor attempted to correct the data post-recovery by using zero readings from the sensor obtained before and after deployment to establish the cumulative drift over time. This was then applied as a linear correction. Note that the data is still suspect as the air values appear to be slightly high at the start of the deployment. * Deployment 10:  Due to a firmware bug, the sensor zeroing function for correcting the baseline drift over time is not currently saving the new reference value to compare the raw CO2 value outputs during the measurements. The sensors are zeroing at the end of the sample cycle when scheduled, but the firmware is not storing the new value. This results in the original zero reference value being used for all measurements and an observable and consistent negative drift in both the air and water CO2 values. The vendor has indicated that the data may be correctable post-recovery, however at this time no such correction algorithm has been provided
